They'd be all over us.

73
00:06:36,985 --> 00:06:40,075
Look, we lay down some fire
to get a head start.

74
00:06:40,104 --> 00:06:42,480
You stay here.
I hop down and draw them away.

75
00:06:42,508 --> 00:06:45,192
That gives you the chance
to get up the bleachers
and out a window.

76
00:06:45,207 --> 00:06:47,629
And where do you go?

77
00:06:47,677 --> 00:06:49,403
<i>Locker room
down those steps.</i>

78
00:06:49,426 --> 00:06:52,221
Looks like a good way
to get trapped.

79
00:06:52,236 --> 00:06:54,553
It's got windows too,
and more my size.

80
00:06:54,555 --> 00:06:58,174
I get out through one,
I double back, we meet up
out on the field.

81
00:06:58,192 --> 00:06:59,865
You're a crazy son
of a bitch, ain't you?

82
00:06:59,903 --> 00:07:02,045
Just trying to do right
for that boy.

83
00:07:02,062 --> 00:07:05,204
You take three shots
and you go.

84
00:07:05,206 --> 00:07:07,774
After that I fire.
I'll lay down a cover for you.

85
00:07:07,808 --> 00:07:09,979
- I'll get you a lead.
- All right.

86
00:07:24,092 --> 00:07:26,025
Oh God.

87
00:07:26,056 --> 00:07:27,559
( Screams )

88
00:08:02,414 --> 00:08:05,002
( Grunting )

89
