92
00:09:23,505 --> 00:09:26,053
( T-Dog shivering )

93
00:09:44,155 --> 00:09:46,272
So do we ring the bell?

94
00:09:46,305 --> 00:09:48,317
I mean it looks like
people live here.

95
00:09:48,362 --> 00:09:50,774
We're past this kind
of stuff, aren't we?

96
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:52,695
Having to be considerate.

97
00:09:52,740 --> 00:09:55,689
Did you close the gate
up the road when you drove in?

98
00:09:55,723 --> 00:09:57,991
Uh, hi.

99
00:09:58,017 --> 00:10:00,090
Yes, we closed it.

100
00:10:00,258 --> 00:10:01,959
Did the latch
and everything.

101
00:10:04,823 --> 00:10:07,340
Hello.
Nice to see you again.

102
00:10:07,374 --> 00:10:11,275
We met before briefly.

103
00:10:11,315 --> 00:10:15,206
Look, we came to help.
There anything we can do?

104
00:10:18,578 --> 00:10:23,236
It's not a bite.
I cut myself pretty bad though.

105
00:10:23,283 --> 00:10:25,144
We'll have it looked at.
I'll tell them you're here.

106
00:10:25,283 --> 00:10:29,758
We have some painkillers
and antibiotics.

107
00:10:29,806 --> 00:10:32,763
I already gave him some.
If Carl needs any.

108
00:10:32,832 --> 00:10:34,409
Come on inside.
I'll make you
something to eat.

109
00:10:45,466 --> 00:10:48,327
<i>( Air hissing )</i>

110
00:10:56,516 --> 00:10:58,065
Hey.

111
00:10:58,187 --> 00:11:00,812
Hey.

112
00:11:02,603 --> 00:11:06,023
Um, we're here, okay?

113
00:11:06,058 --> 00:11:08,089
Thank you.

114
00:11:08,123 --> 00:11:10,387
Whatever you need.

115
00:11:27,895 --> 00:11:27,927
They don't get back soon,
we're gonna have a decision
to make.

116
00:11:31,407 --> 00:11:32,919
And that is?

117
00:11:33,096 --> 00:11:35,614
Whether to operate on your
boy without the respirator.

118
00:11:35,616 --> 00:11:37,595
<i>- You said that wouldn't work.
- I know.</i>

119
00:11:37,629 --> 00:11:41,958
It's extremely unlikely.
But we can't wait much longer.

120
00:11:49,686 --> 00:11:51,848
You really think
we're gonna find Sophia?

121
00:11:55,293 --> 00:11:57,327
You got that look
on your face

122
00:11:57,361 --> 00:11:59,275
same as everybody else.

123
00:11:59,313 --> 00:12:01,193
What the hell's wrong
with you people?

124
00:12:01,228 --> 00:12:04,016
- We just started looking.
- Well, do you?

125
00:12:04,067 --> 00:12:07,572
It ain't
the mountains of Tibet.
It's Georgia.

126
00:12:07,606 --> 00:12:10,125
She could be holed up
in a farmhouse somewhere.

127
00:12:10,169 --> 00:12:12,209
People get lost
and they survive.

128
00:12:12,243 --> 00:12:15,261
- It happens all the time.
- She's only 12.

129
00:12:15,307 --> 00:12:17,521
Hell, I was younger
than her and I got lost.

130
00:12:17,540 --> 00:12:20,452
Nine days in the woods
eating berries,

131
00:12:20,486 --> 00:12:22,593
wiping my ass
with poison oak.

132
00:12:22,622 --> 00:12:24,564
They found you?

133
00:12:24,589 --> 00:12:27,439
My old man was off on
a bender with some waitress.

134
00:12:27,451 --> 00:12:30,253
Merle was doing another
stint in juvie.

135
00:12:30,278 --> 00:12:32,641
Didn't even know
I was gone.

136
00:12:32,672 --> 00:12:34,890
I made my way back though.

137
00:12:34,926 --> 00:12:37,516
Went straight into the kitchen
and made myself a sandwich.

138
00:12:37,552 --> 00:12:40,395
No worse for wear.

139
00:12:40,452 --> 00:12:43,281
Except my ass itched
something awful.

140
00:12:43,336 --> 00:12:45,233
( Laughs )

141
00:12:45,267 --> 00:12:47,046
I'm sorry.

142
00:12:47,078 --> 00:12:49,052
I'm sorry, that is
a terrible story.

143
00:12:49,086 --> 00:12:52,180
( Both laugh )

144
00:12:52,214 --> 00:12:55,394
Only difference is Sophia's
got people looking for her.

145
00:12:55,465 --> 00:12:58,155
I call that an advantage.

146
00:13:12,195 --> 00:13:15,148
Maybe this isn't a world
for children anymore.

147
00:13:16,308 --> 00:13:18,387
Yeah well,
we have a child.

148
00:13:18,410 --> 00:13:20,538
Carl is here
in this world now.

149
00:13:20,728 --> 00:13:22,143
Maybe he shouldn't be.

150
00:13:22,342 --> 00:13:24,598
Maybe this is how
it's supposed to be.

151
00:13:27,684 --> 00:13:29,353
You can't mean that.

152
00:13:33,668 --> 00:13:35,554
Okay.
All right.

153
00:13:35,606 --> 00:13:37,817
I can understand that
thought crossing your mind.

154
00:13:37,867 --> 00:13:40,742
It didn't cross my mind, Rick.
I can't stop thinking it.

155
00:13:40,776 --> 00:13:43,952
Why do we want Carl
to live in this world?

156
00:13:43,985 --> 00:13:46,191
To have this life?

157
00:13:46,225 --> 00:13:49,926
So he can see more people
torn apart in front of him?

158
00:13:49,928 --> 00:13:52,749
So that he can be
hungry and scared

159
00:13:52,772 --> 00:13:55,930
for however long
he has before he...

160
00:13:57,274 --> 00:14:01,207
So he can run and run
and run and run

161
00:14:01,209 --> 00:14:04,087
and then even if he
survives he ends up...

162
00:14:06,545 --> 00:14:09,778
he ends up just another
animal who doesn't know
anything except survival?

163
00:14:09,812 --> 00:14:12,549
If he...

164
00:14:12,590 --> 00:14:15,728
if he dies tonight,

165
00:14:15,762 --> 00:14:18,382
it ends for him.

166
00:14:18,416 --> 00:14:21,185
Tell me why it would
be better another way.

167
00:14:25,490 --> 00:14:28,061
What changed?

168
00:14:28,063 --> 00:14:30,193
What?

169
00:14:30,220 --> 00:14:33,747
Jenner offered us
a way out.

170
00:14:33,763 --> 00:14:35,733
You asked him
to let us keep trying.

171
00:14:35,892 --> 00:14:37,570
You begged him.

172
00:14:37,572 --> 00:14:40,091
"For as long
as we can," you said.
What changed?

173
00:14:40,093 --> 00:14:41,685
There was a moment
the other day...

174
00:14:41,719 --> 00:14:44,967
it was just a second
but I forgot Jacqui was dead.

175
00:14:45,001 --> 00:14:47,758
I turned around,
I wanted to tell
her something.

176
00:14:47,789 --> 00:14:51,108
I almost said her name.
It was just a second
and then I remembered.

177
00:14:51,130 --> 00:14:53,763
But then I realized she
didn't have to see any of it.

178
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:59,350
The highway, the herds,
Sophia, Carl getting shot...

179
00:14:59,384 --> 00:15:02,172
she didn't...

180
00:15:04,167 --> 00:15:07,304
She doesn't have
to be afraid anymore.

181
00:15:07,306 --> 00:15:09,649
Hungry.
Angry.

182
00:15:09,877 --> 00:15:12,528
It hasn't stopped
happening, Rick.

183
00:15:12,622 --> 00:15:16,069
It's like we live with
a knife at our throats
every second of every day.

184
00:15:16,103 --> 00:15:18,969
But Jacqui doesn't.
Not anymore.

185
00:15:19,007 --> 00:15:21,581
And then...

186
00:15:23,656 --> 00:15:25,949
I thought,
"maybe Jenner was right."

187
00:15:29,749 --> 00:15:32,479
I don't accept that.

188
00:15:32,513 --> 00:15:34,527
I can't accept that.

189
00:15:34,545 --> 00:15:37,306
That man surrendered.
It doesn't Matt...

190
00:15:37,498 --> 00:15:41,164
it doesn't matter
what he said.

191
00:15:41,184 --> 00:15:43,195
None of it.

192
00:15:43,197 --> 00:15:46,717
You really think it would
be better if Carl...

193
00:15:51,169 --> 00:15:54,394
if we just gave up?

194
00:15:54,428 --> 00:15:58,702
Tell me why it would
be better the other way.

195
00:16:01,365 --> 00:16:03,668
Please.

196
00:16:11,479 --> 00:16:14,014
<i>( Walkers moaning )</i>

197
00:17:15,670 --> 00:17:17,515
( Gunshot )

198
00:17:26,612 --> 00:17:29,207
Man, I thought
I'd lost you.

199
00:17:29,253 --> 00:17:31,052
That was my last
rifle round.

200
00:17:31,057 --> 00:17:33,120
- Mine too.
- Come on.

201
00:17:33,138 --> 00:17:34,582
Come on.
Come on.

202
00:17:51,836 --> 00:17:54,680
<i>( Carl coughing )</i>

203
00:17:59,721 --> 00:18:03,108
- Where are we?
- Hey, little man.

204
00:18:03,137 --> 00:18:05,352
That's Hershel.

205
00:18:05,548 --> 00:18:07,868
We're in his house.

206
00:18:07,907 --> 00:18:10,152
You had an accident.

207
00:18:10,190 --> 00:18:13,160
- All right?
- It hurts, a lot.

208
00:18:13,194 --> 00:18:15,682
Oh baby, I know.
I know.

209
00:18:17,423 --> 00:18:19,831
- You should have seen it.
- What?

210
00:18:19,865 --> 00:18:22,201
The deer.

211
00:18:22,236 --> 00:18:24,815
<i>It was so pretty, mom.</i>

212
00:18:24,849 --> 00:18:27,679
It was so close.

213
00:18:27,735 --> 00:18:30,777
I've never been...

214
00:18:38,172 --> 00:18:39,446
Carl?

215
00:18:39,632 --> 00:18:41,628
What is happening?

216
00:18:41,784 --> 00:18:44,497
- ( Grunting )
- Don't. It's a seizure.

217
00:18:44,531 --> 00:18:46,432
If you hold him down,
you could hurt him.

218
00:18:46,466 --> 00:18:48,811
- You can't stop it?
- He has to just go through it.

219
00:18:52,658 --> 00:18:55,583
<i>( Lori sobbing )</i>

220
00:19:08,336 --> 00:19:11,070
His brain isn't
getting enough blood.

221
00:19:11,104 --> 00:19:13,937
His pressure is bottoming.
He needs another transfusion.

222
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:16,538
- Okay, I'm ready.
- If I take any more
out of you

223
00:19:16,572 --> 00:19:18,822
your body could shut down.
You could go into a coma.

224
00:19:18,856 --> 00:19:22,317
<i>- Or cardiac arrest.
- You're wasting time.</i>

225
00:19:44,378 --> 00:19:47,167
Come on, man.
We need a way out.

226
00:19:47,197 --> 00:19:49,096
( Gasping )

227
00:19:49,150 --> 00:19:52,341
- Just let me
catch my breath.
- Come on.

228
00:19:53,988 --> 00:19:56,328
- ( Growling )
- ( Gasps )

229
00:20:16,023 --> 00:20:18,364
<i>( Stairs clinking )</i>

230
00:20:24,236 --> 00:20:26,151
Can't sleep?

231
00:20:26,156 --> 00:20:30,497
I'm gonna wait for them
to come back.

232
00:20:32,279 --> 00:20:34,177
You can go down and sleep
if you want to.

233
00:20:34,218 --> 00:20:37,096
No, we can
keep watch together.

234
00:20:41,121 --> 00:20:43,109
Which way did they go?

235
00:20:55,524 --> 00:20:57,800
<i>( Rustling )</i>

236
00:21:13,393 --> 00:21:15,904
( Rustling )

237
00:21:22,870 --> 00:21:25,314
What the hell?

238
00:21:29,557 --> 00:21:31,599
( Gagging )

239
00:21:33,527 --> 00:21:35,625
"Got bit.
Fever hit.

240
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:38,201
World gone to shit.
Might as well quit."

241
00:21:38,285 --> 00:21:40,668
Dumbass didn't know enough
to shoot himself in the head.

242
00:21:40,702 --> 00:21:43,987
Turned himself into a big
swinging piece of bait.

243
00:21:44,021 --> 00:21:45,637
And a mess.

244
00:21:45,671 --> 00:21:48,626
<i>- ( Groans )
- You all right?</i>

245
00:21:48,645 --> 00:21:51,106
Trying not to puke.

246
00:21:51,140 --> 00:21:54,264
- Go ahead if you gotta.
- No, I'm fine.

247
00:21:54,447 --> 00:21:56,917
Let's just talk about
something else for a minute.

248
00:21:56,919 --> 00:21:59,963
- How'd you learn to shoot?
- Gotta eat.

249
00:22:00,082 --> 00:22:02,596
That's one thing these walkers
and us have in common.

250
00:22:02,612 --> 00:22:06,987
<i>I guess it's the closest
he's been to food since
he turned.</i>

251
00:22:07,024 --> 00:22:10,020
Hanging up there
like a big pinata.

252
00:22:10,044 --> 00:22:12,675
<i>The other geeks came and ate
all the flesh off his legs.</i>

253
00:22:12,709 --> 00:22:15,685
( Vomits, coughs )

254
00:22:15,705 --> 00:22:19,380
I thought we were
changing the subject.

255
00:22:19,429 --> 00:22:22,795
Call that payback for
laughing about my itchy ass.

256
00:22:22,829 --> 00:22:25,504
There wasn't a lot
that came up.

257
00:22:27,019 --> 00:22:28,876
Huh.

258
00:22:28,961 --> 00:22:30,942
Let's head back.

259
00:22:30,979 --> 00:22:33,837
Aren't you gonna...

260
00:22:33,874 --> 00:22:36,253
No.
He ain't hurting nobody.

261
00:22:36,277 --> 00:22:38,615
<i>Ain't gonna waste
an arrow either.</i>

262
00:22:38,652 --> 00:22:41,105
<i>He made his choice.
Opted out.</i>

263
00:22:41,117 --> 00:22:43,513
Let him hang.

264
00:22:57,973 --> 00:23:01,180
You want to live now
or not?

265
00:23:02,334 --> 00:23:04,609
It's just a question.

266
00:23:09,531 --> 00:23:11,731
An answer for an arrow.

267
00:23:11,733 --> 00:23:13,037
Fair?

268
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:17,912
I don't know
if I want to live

269
00:23:18,145 --> 00:23:21,000
or if I have to

270
00:23:21,002 --> 00:23:23,498
or if it's just a habit.

271
00:23:25,813 --> 00:23:28,105
Not much of an answer.

272
00:23:33,946 --> 00:23:36,039
Waste of an arrow.

273
00:23:48,676 --> 00:23:51,837
<i>You don't need to worry.
She's with Daryl.</i>

274
00:23:51,883 --> 00:23:54,317
If something happens
he can protect her.

275
00:23:54,558 --> 00:23:56,286
<i>You hear what I'm saying?</i>

276
00:23:56,332 --> 00:23:59,047
Sorry, all I heard was
if something happens.

277
00:24:03,254 --> 00:24:04,493
You mind keeping watch?

278
00:24:04,527 --> 00:24:06,417
I don't know how
to use that.

279
00:24:06,476 --> 00:24:08,210
I won't be gone long.

280
00:24:08,229 --> 00:24:10,678
If you see anything, call out.

281
00:24:10,731 --> 00:24:13,577
I'm not going far.
I'll hear you.

282
00:24:25,326 --> 00:24:27,459
You got here
right in time.

283
00:24:27,510 --> 00:24:30,047
This couldn't go
untreated much longer.

284
00:24:34,261 --> 00:24:35,742
"Merle Dixon."

285
00:24:35,849 --> 00:24:38,552
Is that your friend
with the antibiotics?

286
00:24:38,574 --> 00:24:40,906
No, ma'am.
Merle's no longer with us.

287
00:24:40,908 --> 00:24:43,411
Daryl gave us those...
his brother.

288
00:24:43,413 --> 00:24:45,169
Not sure I'd call
him a friend.

289
00:24:45,282 --> 00:24:48,135
He is today.
This doxycycline might have
just saved your life.

290
00:24:48,169 --> 00:24:50,609
You know what merle
was taking it for?

291
00:24:50,660 --> 00:24:52,537
The clap.

292
00:24:52,571 --> 00:24:55,431
Um, venereal disease.

293
00:24:55,496 --> 00:24:57,513
That's what Daryl said.

294
00:24:57,595 --> 00:25:00,724
I'd say merle Dixon's
clap was the best thing
to ever happen to you.

295
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:03,050
I'm really trying
not to think about that.

296
00:25:28,595 --> 00:25:30,938
Are you praying?

297
00:25:33,871 --> 00:25:36,586
Why do you sneak up
on people so much?

298
00:25:36,597 --> 00:25:38,823
You're easy
to sneak up on.

299
00:25:40,611 --> 00:25:42,485
I was praying.

300
00:25:42,496 --> 00:25:44,641
I was trying to.

301
00:25:44,841 --> 00:25:47,359
You religious?
You pray a lot?

302
00:25:47,467 --> 00:25:51,136
Actually this was
my first try.

303
00:25:51,170 --> 00:25:52,363
Ever?

304
00:25:53,470 --> 00:25:55,296
Wow. Sorry.

305
00:25:55,319 --> 00:25:57,478
I didn't mean to wreck
your first time.

306
00:25:57,625 --> 00:25:59,888
God probably got the gist.

307
00:25:59,890 --> 00:26:02,696
<i>- Praying for what?
- My friends.</i>

308
00:26:02,733 --> 00:26:05,149
Looks like they could all
use a little help right now.

309
00:26:09,884 --> 00:26:11,548
You think...

310
00:26:11,716 --> 00:26:14,617
you think God exists?

311
00:26:14,655 --> 00:26:17,140
I always took it
on faith.

312
00:26:17,190 --> 00:26:19,686
Lately I've wondered.

313
00:26:19,688 --> 00:26:21,906
Everything that's happened,

314
00:26:22,074 --> 00:26:24,113
there must have been a lot
of praying going on.

315
00:26:24,208 --> 00:26:27,266
It seems quite a few
went unanswered.

316
00:26:28,737 --> 00:26:31,017
Thanks.
This is really helping.

317
00:26:31,103 --> 00:26:33,615
Sorry.
Go ahead.

318
00:26:33,617 --> 00:26:35,842
<i>Really.</i>

319
00:26:39,378 --> 00:26:41,144
You gonna watch?

320
00:26:46,021 --> 00:26:48,585
I'll get you
a refill instead.

321
00:26:55,575 --> 00:26:57,866
I know it's not my business,

322
00:26:57,868 --> 00:26:59,895
and feel free
to believe in God,

323
00:26:59,915 --> 00:27:03,333
but the thing is
you've got to make it
okay somehow

324
00:27:03,367 --> 00:27:06,377
no matter what happens.

325
00:27:51,905 --> 00:27:54,247
Before it happened

326
00:27:54,269 --> 00:27:57,741
we were standing there
in the woods

327
00:27:57,777 --> 00:28:01,243
and this deer

328
00:28:01,245 --> 00:28:03,631
just crossed
right in front of us.

329
00:28:03,727 --> 00:28:07,279
I swear it just
planted itself there

330
00:28:07,435 --> 00:28:10,785
and looked Carl
right in the eye.

331
00:28:10,787 --> 00:28:13,766
And I looked at Carl

332
00:28:13,768 --> 00:28:16,849
looking at that deer,
and that deer looking
right back at Carl.

333
00:28:16,933 --> 00:28:18,831
And that moment just...

334
00:28:18,875 --> 00:28:21,387
( Sighs )

335
00:28:25,197 --> 00:28:27,795
Slipped away.

336
00:28:27,797 --> 00:28:30,348
It slipped away.

337
00:28:30,397 --> 00:28:34,448
That's what he was talking
about when he woke up,

338
00:28:36,161 --> 00:28:37,909
not about getting shot

339
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:40,673
or what happened
at the church.

340
00:28:42,210 --> 00:28:43,992
He talked about
something beautiful,

341
00:28:44,026 --> 00:28:46,712
something living.

342
00:28:46,758 --> 00:28:49,859
There's still
a life for us,

343
00:28:49,905 --> 00:28:52,517
a place maybe like this.

344
00:28:52,629 --> 00:28:55,581
It isn't all death
out there.

345
00:28:55,689 --> 00:28:57,936
It can't be.

346
00:28:58,052 --> 00:28:59,712
We just have to be
strong enough

347
00:28:59,714 --> 00:29:03,260
after everything we've seen
to still believe that.

348
00:29:03,301 --> 00:29:06,863
Why is it better for Carl
to live even in this world?

349
00:29:09,196 --> 00:29:13,490
He talked about
the deer, Lori.

350
00:29:13,524 --> 00:29:15,764
<i>He talked about
the deer.</i>

351
00:29:21,017 --> 00:29:22,409
<i>Shane:
Oh, shit.</i>

352
00:29:22,443 --> 00:29:25,645
( Both groan )

353
00:29:25,686 --> 00:29:28,479
Got to get to the street,
double back to the truck.

354
00:29:28,529 --> 00:29:31,046
- Look, we ain't
gonna make it, okay?
- Got to try, man.

355
00:29:31,077 --> 00:29:33,316
- Come on, get up.
- You're gonna take these bags

356
00:29:33,370 --> 00:29:35,970
- and you're gonna go.
- I ain't leaving you behind.

357
00:29:38,430 --> 00:29:39,757
Okay.

358
00:29:43,717 --> 00:29:45,940
How many rounds
you got left?

359
00:29:45,968 --> 00:29:47,713
Four. You?

360
00:29:47,736 --> 00:29:49,957
Five and one in the pipe.

361
00:29:49,990 --> 00:29:52,535
( Snarling, growling )

362
00:29:57,377 --> 00:29:59,710
( Gunshot )

363
00:30:02,213 --> 00:30:04,031
( Gunshot )

364
00:30:12,166 --> 00:30:15,846
He's still losing blood
faster than we can replace it.

365
00:30:15,880 --> 00:30:18,152
And with the swelling
in his abdomen

366
00:30:18,212 --> 00:30:20,206
we can't wait any longer

367
00:30:20,251 --> 00:30:22,296
or he's just going
to slip away.

368
00:30:22,325 --> 00:30:24,842
Now I need to know right now

369
00:30:24,877 --> 00:30:26,938
if you want me to do this,

370
00:30:26,942 --> 00:30:29,485
because I think your boy
is out of time.

371
00:30:32,138 --> 00:30:33,297
You have to make a choice.

372
00:30:33,304 --> 00:30:35,937
- A choice?
- A choice.

373
00:30:35,951 --> 00:30:39,441
You have to tell me
what it is.

374
00:30:39,443 --> 00:30:41,554
You have to
tell me what it is.

375
00:30:47,472 --> 00:30:49,015
We do it.

376
00:30:58,232 --> 00:31:00,218
Okay, get the corner
of that bed.

377
00:31:00,252 --> 00:31:01,931
Let's get the sheets down.

378
00:31:01,939 --> 00:31:04,647
Get the I.V. bag
on the sheet.

379
00:31:04,686 --> 00:31:08,534
<i>Okay, on three.</i>

380
00:31:08,568 --> 00:31:11,524
One, two, three.

381
00:31:30,680 --> 00:31:32,903
Rick, Lori,

382
00:31:32,937 --> 00:31:34,951
you may want to step out.

383
00:31:36,664 --> 00:31:38,710
<i>( Truck approaching )</i>

384
00:31:42,254 --> 00:31:44,196
<i>Rick:
Oh God.</i>

385
00:31:44,226 --> 00:31:46,697
You stay here with him.

386
00:31:59,358 --> 00:32:02,106
- Carl?
- There's still a chance.

387
00:32:05,399 --> 00:32:07,416
Otis?

388
00:32:09,293 --> 00:32:11,223
No.

389
00:32:18,508 --> 00:32:20,524
We say nothing to Patricia.

390
00:32:20,550 --> 00:32:23,975
Not till after.
I need her.

391
00:32:41,762 --> 00:32:45,155
They kept blocking us
at every turn.

392
00:32:45,208 --> 00:32:47,860
We had nothing left.
We were down to 10 rounds.

393
00:32:47,862 --> 00:32:50,452
Then he said...
he said he'd cover me

394
00:32:50,486 --> 00:32:52,210
and that I should
keep going.

395
00:32:52,427 --> 00:32:54,947
So that's what I did.
I just...

396
00:32:54,969 --> 00:32:57,586
I kept going.
But I...

397
00:32:59,934 --> 00:33:03,196
I looked back and he...

398
00:33:07,663 --> 00:33:09,831
I tried.

399
00:33:09,879 --> 00:33:12,467
He wanted to make it right.

400
00:33:19,099 --> 00:33:21,879
( Crying )

401
00:34:01,865 --> 00:34:04,462
Andrea.
Wait.

402
00:34:04,592 --> 00:34:06,496
What do you want, Dale?

403
00:34:06,530 --> 00:34:09,043
To give you this.

404
00:34:09,106 --> 00:34:11,122
<i>I care about you</i>

405
00:34:11,156 --> 00:34:14,065
so I made a choice
for you...  choices.

406
00:34:14,099 --> 00:34:17,977
I know why I did it,
but this is not my gun.

407
00:34:18,011 --> 00:34:20,867
And the choices
that I made for you

408
00:34:20,869 --> 00:34:22,372
were not mine to make.

409
00:34:29,580 --> 00:34:31,719
But I can still ask,

410
00:34:31,876 --> 00:34:34,297
and this is not
to make you guilty

411
00:34:34,331 --> 00:34:37,110
or put me ahead of you,
but I can still ask,

412
00:34:38,816 --> 00:34:40,292
please...

413
00:34:41,692 --> 00:34:44,486
Don't make me regret this.

414
00:34:48,136 --> 00:34:49,595
I'll take watch.

415
00:34:51,196 --> 00:34:53,219
So do you forgive
me for...

416
00:34:57,055 --> 00:34:59,166
do you forgive me?

417
00:35:00,290 --> 00:35:02,698
I'm trying.

418
00:35:13,546 --> 00:35:16,999
I've known Otis
since I was a kid.

419
00:35:17,105 --> 00:35:20,664
He's run this farm
since before my mother died.

420
00:35:30,500 --> 00:35:33,002
Who else?

421
00:35:33,036 --> 00:35:35,777
Who'd you lose?

422
00:35:39,009 --> 00:35:41,573
You told me I had
to make it okay somehow.

423
00:35:43,195 --> 00:35:45,697
That's what you've been
trying to do, right?

424
00:35:45,731 --> 00:35:47,670
Which ones?

425
00:35:53,803 --> 00:35:55,592
Stepmother.

426
00:35:58,708 --> 00:36:01,344
Stepbrother.

427
00:36:15,961 --> 00:36:18,433
He seems to have
stabilized.

428
00:36:18,466 --> 00:36:20,277
( Exhales )
Oh God.

429
00:36:31,347 --> 00:36:33,686
I don't have words.

430
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:35,908
I don't either.
Wish I did.

431
00:36:37,977 --> 00:36:40,203
How do I tell Patricia
about Otis?

432
00:36:44,150 --> 00:36:46,527
You go to Carl.

433
00:36:47,788 --> 00:36:49,878
I'll go with Hershel.

434
00:37:15,168 --> 00:37:17,926
( Patricia sobbing )

435
00:37:38,918 --> 00:37:41,605
( Sobbing )

436
00:38:08,401 --> 00:38:10,348
Stay.

437
00:38:49,136 --> 00:38:51,624
The bathroom's upstairs.

438
00:38:51,676 --> 00:38:54,717
- I brought you some clothes.
- Thank you.

439
00:38:54,825 --> 00:38:57,428
They won't fit well.
They were Otis's.

440
00:39:48,333 --> 00:39:51,242
<i>Shane:
How many rounds
you got left?</i>

441
00:39:51,307 --> 00:39:53,657
<i>Otis:
Four. You?</i>

442
00:39:53,659 --> 00:39:56,571
<i>Shane:
Five and one in the pipe.</i>

443
00:39:56,573 --> 00:39:59,348
( Groans )
Come on.

444
00:40:22,675 --> 00:40:25,502
( Panting )

445
00:40:49,725 --> 00:40:52,622
- Down to my last.
- Me too.

446
00:40:55,412 --> 00:40:56,866
I'm sorry.

447
00:40:59,007 --> 00:41:01,391
- ( Gunshot )
- ( Screams )

448
00:41:01,421 --> 00:41:03,591
( Growling )

449
00:41:05,359 --> 00:41:07,549
Will you give it...  ah!

450
00:41:07,567 --> 00:41:09,566
Give it!

451
00:41:09,613 --> 00:41:12,022
( Otis screaming )

452
00:41:17,271 --> 00:41:18,900
I'll kill you.

453
00:41:18,948 --> 00:41:21,512
( Shane screams )

454
00:41:30,727 --> 00:41:32,358
( Screams )

455
00:41:41,700 --> 00:41:44,128
Let go of me!
Let go!

456
00:41:51,636 --> 00:41:54,271
<i>( Otis screaming )</i>

457
00:42:08,680 --> 00:42:10,937
( Panting )

